<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>26016</anchor> <rss>anon.255.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.255</addr>  <route>anon.255.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>It <link href="jms-0027.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0027" title="Positively generated dcpos have open positivity predicates">suffices</link> to recall that a <link href="jms-0025.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0025" title="Lifted dcpos are positively generated">lifted dcpo is positively generated</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>26017</anchor> <rss>jms-0024.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>jms-0024</addr>  <route>jms-0024.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>2</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Lifted dcpos have open positivity predicates</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be a dcpo; then the lifting <tex>\mathsf { L } {A}</tex> has an <link href="jms-0022.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0022" title="Open positivity predicate">open positivity predicate</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>26018</anchor> <rss>jms-0025.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-0025</addr>  <route>jms-0025.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>2</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Lifted dcpos are positively generated</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be a dcpo; then the lift <tex>\mathsf { L } {A}</tex> is <link href="jms-0023.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0023" title="Positively generated dcpos">positively generated</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>26019</anchor> <rss>anon.254.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.254</addr>  <route>anon.254.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>Let <tex>u= { \mathopen {} \left ( \phi ,a \right ) \mathclose {}}</tex> be an element of <tex>\mathsf { L } {A}</tex>. Note that <tex>u</tex> is equal to <tex>\bigsqcup _{p: \phi }u</tex>; as <link href="jms-001N.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001N" title="Positivity = definedness in a lifted dcpo">definedness coincides with positivity</link> in lifted dcpos, we have <tex>\phi  =  \mathsf { pos } \, u</tex>, and so we are done.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>26020</anchor> <rss>jms-0027.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-0027</addr>  <route>jms-0027.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>2</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tomdejong.xml" type="local" tomdejong="addr">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martinescardo.xml" type="local" martinescardo="addr">Martín Hötzel Escardó</link></author><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Positively generated dcpos have open positivity predicates</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be a <link href="jms-0023.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0023" title="Positively generated dcpos">positively generated</link> <link href="jms-001S.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001S" title="Pointed dcpo">pointed</link> dcpo. Then <tex>A</tex> has an <link href="jms-0022.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0022" title="Open positivity predicate">open positivity predicate</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>26021</anchor> <rss>anon.252.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.252</addr>  <route>anon.252.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>Let <tex>I \subseteq  A</tex> be a directed subset such that <tex>\bigsqcup {I}</tex> is positive; we must find a positive element of <tex>I</tex>. Because <tex>A</tex> is <link href="jms-0023.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0023" title="Positively generated dcpos">positively generated</link> we know that <tex>\bigsqcup {I}  \sqsubseteq   \bigsqcup { \mathopen {} \left ( I \cap  A^+ \right ) \mathclose {}}</tex>. Because <tex>\bigsqcup {I}</tex> is positive and <tex>I \cap  A^+</tex> <link href="jms-0028.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0028" title="The positive part of a semidirected subset is semidirected">is semidirected</link>, it follows that the latter is inhabited.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>